ce:section.ce:para:
A series of TA-NCDs, namely, TA-NCDs-1 to TA-NCDs-5 (seen Table 1
                        ), were synthesized by hydrothermal method from tartaric acid and 3-aminophenol (shown in Fig. 1
                        a). The transmission electron microscopy (TEM) images show that TA-NCDs had typical sphere-like morphology, and their average diameters are all around 5–6 nm (Fig. 1b and S1). Corresponding particle size distribution diagram are in accordance with TEM results. The high-resolution transmission electron microscopy (HRTEM) images confirmed that TA-NCDs all have 0.21 nm interplanar spacing assigned to the (100) lattice plane of graphite, illustrating that they all have a graphite-like structure and are well crystallized [12,13].
